The paper focuses on the application of machine learning algorithms for gas demand forecasting, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the pre-processing and feature extraction steps, which are relevant to data science (cs.DS) and computational engineering (cs.CE). Additionally, the paper discusses the role of temperature forecasts in gas demand forecasting, which could be considered a topic in statistical inference (cs.SI).
